 late M dwarfs show no systematic difference from our\nresults for the early and middle M dwarfs, and confirm the higher O/C ratio at\nthe lower metallicity. In late M dwarfs, CO and H2O remain as excellent\nabundance indicators of C and O, respectively, except for additional\nuncertainty due to the complexity associated with the dust formation in the\nlatest M dwarfs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 15 Nov 2015 10:57:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-01-20"}
